# Iterative Fibonacci via `var` + `while`

R.2.2 lowers `var x: T = init` to `let mut x: T = init`,
reassignments via `x = e`, and `while (cond) body` to Rust `while`.

```scalascript
def fibIter(n: Long): Long =
  var a: Long = 0
  var b: Long = 1
  var i: Long = 0
  while (i < n) {
    val t: Long = a + b
    a = b
    b = t
    i = i + 1
  }
  a

@main def run(): Unit = println(fibIter(10))
```

Build and run:

```bash
ssc build-rust while-fib.ssc
./while-fib                  # → 55
```
